section.section:
The Board may authorize, by regulation, the transporting of human specimens under its exclusive control to an out-of-state medical study program, provided that:
The needs of the schools of the State are met;
The requesting party demonstrates the need for a specimen;
The circumstances of the request are that:
The requesting party bears the responsibility for transporting and the specialized care of the specimen and all associated costs; and
The Board retains the right of exclusive control of the specimen including the final disposition when appropriate or necessary to fulfill an obligation to return the remains of a donated specimen to the donor's family.
